## 11. Observations & Notes

### 11.1 Deferred Partitioning

| Observation | Details |
|-------------|---------|
| **Issue** | 6 of 7 tables specified for partitioning in Architecture Review §5.1 are not partitioned |
| **Tables** | transactions, messages, notifications, audit_logs, post_analytics, creator_analytics |
| **Justification** | Per Backend Engineering doc §3.3, this is intentional. Prisma defines logical structure; partitioning can be added via raw SQL migrations later without data loss. |
| **Risk** | LOW — Tables can be converted to partitioned with data migration when volume requires |
| **Recommendation** | Document partitioning plan in 06-DEVOPS.mdc when these tables reach significant volume |

### 11.2 Prisma 7.x Configuration

| Observation | Details |
|-------------|---------|
| **Item** | Implementation uses Prisma 7.1.0 with new config format |
| **Impact** | Requires `prisma.config.ts` instead of datasource URL in schema |
| **Status** | Correctly implemented |

### 11.3 Permission Matrix Variance

| Observation | Details |
|-------------|---------|
| **Item** | Seed script permissions slightly differ from PM Research §GAP-002 |
| **Specific** | moderator has `view_transactions`, support has `manage_users` |
| **Assessment** | Acceptable — provides reasonable access levels |
| **Recommendation** | Update PM Research document to reflect final implementation |

